Still Game is to return to Scotland's TV screens next month with an hour-long version of their live stage show. Still Game set for TV return Still Game is to return to Scotland's TV screens next month with an hour-long version of their live stage show.The sitcom played for a 21-night run at Glasgow's Hydro arena,and was seen by more than 200,000 people.The TV show will be shown on BBC1 Scotland on Friday, November 7.Forty-four episodes of Still Game were broadcast over six series from 2002.In the show, Ford Keirnan and Greg Hemphill played Jack Jarvis and Victor McDade, pensioners living in the fictional Glasgow housing scheme of Craiglang.It is seven years since the TV show was last recorded. 